A curious and quite complex song consisting of variable number of high-pitch notes followed by a sequence of high-then-low-pitch note pairs. Between these series, a protracted high-pitch whistle terminated by an abrupt, almost metallic sound can be heard. I suspect this latter sound sequence could be an attempt to imitate some mechanical sound the bird could have heard in the town environment.
The bird was seen on a branch of a birch tree in a residential district of the town. Cloudy winter day with no wind and no precipitation.
